
# Mobile UI Optimization & Shorts Tab Implementation

Refining the mobile experience for VibeStream and integrating a dedicated Shorts tab for quick discovery, mirroring industry leaders.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Navigation Change**: I am adding a "Shorts" tab to the mobile bottom navigation. To keep the UI clean, I will consolidate "Saved" into the profile/you tab, following YouTube's "Home, Shorts, (+), Subscriptions, You" layout.

## Proposed Changes

### Navigation Components
#### [MODIFY] [MobileNav.tsx](file:///C:/GOLive/components/MobileNav.tsx)
- **Shorts Tab**: Add "Shorts" with a central focus.
- **Label Polish**: Refine text sizes and spacing for better readability on small screens.
- **YouTube Layout**: Reorder to `Home, Shorts, (+), Following, You`.

#### [DELETE] [BottomNav.tsx](file:///C:/GOLive/components/BottomNav.tsx) [NEW]
- Remove redundant navigation component to clean up the codebase.

### Header Optimization
#### [MODIFY] [Navbar.tsx](file:///C:/GOLive/components/Navbar.tsx)
- Hide "VIBESTREAM" text on very small screens (under 360px) to prevent layout shifting.
- Optimize spacing between icons for fat-finger friendliness on mobile.

## Verification Plan

### Automated/Subagent Tests
- **Mobile Viewport Test**: Verify bottom nav layout on 375px and 430px viewports.
- **Shorts Navigation**: Click "Shorts" on mobile and verify it loads the feed correctly.
- **Responsiveness**: Verify the header doesn't wrap or break on small screens.
